    <parallel-group>C-G3</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build the full Pinned Memory Management UI in the Context pane per Q7 scope
    expansion. Components:
    1. **PinnedMemoryListWidget** — Context pane widget showing all pinned items
       grouped by `pinType` (user-preference / system-rule / matter-fact). Filter by
       pinType + matter. Search by title.
    2. **PinnedMemoryEditDialog** — Fluent v9 dialog for create / edit pinned items.
       Fields: title, content (multi-line), pinType (radio), matterId (lookup, optional
       for matter-fact only).
    3. **PinnedMemoryDeleteConfirmation** — confirm before delete; emphasize
       cross-session impact.
    4. **PinnedMemoryProvenanceBadge** — on each item, show "Created via chat: 'remember
       X'" vs "Created via UI" so users understand source.

    All components in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` per ADR-012; Fluent v9; light + dark mode
    parity per ADR-021. Consumes `IPinnedContextService` via a thin BFF endpoint pair
    (add to `WorkspaceStateEndpoints.cs` or sibling). Integrated with Pillar 6a workspace
    state — pinned items DO appear in agent prompt assembly per task 067 composition.

    **SCOPE EXPANSION NOTE**: Per spec Q7 + plan.md §2 Decision Q7, full memory UI was
    originally R7-deferred. Owner approved scope expansion to R6 (2026-06-07); Phase C
    +1-2 weeks. This task is the single largest Phase C frontend task.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React/Fluent-v9 engineer with experience in CRUD UI patterns + dialog
    workflows + accessibility + dark-mode component design.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Full Pinned Memory UI shipped; users can create/edit/delete pinned items via UI
    (in addition to voice commands from task 069); list view shows all items grouped +
    filterable; persistence verified; dark-mode parity verified; integrates with workspace
    state model.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
